                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12767302" author="bosschaert" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2009 11:50:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am starting to look into this one now...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12767814" author="bosschaert" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2009 14:03:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch (jmx_4.patch) contains an implementation of this. The shape of it is pretty much similar to how this is done for the Features Service MBean: it&apos;s in a bundle of its own.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unit tests included for all new code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Main thing missing is to make this new bundle part of the assembly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12768162" author="bosschaert" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2009 10:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The admin-management-assembly patch contains the bits needed to include the new admin-management bundle in the assembly and make it part of the default startup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12768181" author="gnt" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2009 11:32:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder if we should refactor the admin service as we did for the features service, i.e. split in 3 bundles: service, commands and management.&lt;br/&gt;
Thoughts ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12768185" author="bosschaert" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2009 11:44:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least that would be consistent &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; It could easily be done after applying this patch as this one already provides the management portion of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess the one reservation I would have is that Karaf is becoming quite large in terms of the number bundles. But if nobody has an issue with that I&apos;d say we should do the refactor as you suggested...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12768789" author="gnt" created="Thu, 22 Oct 2009 18:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=828802&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=828802&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
